# Frontend Development Rules

## Tech Stack
- React 19 + Vite + TypeScript
- React Router for routing
- Recharts for charts
- Styling via `src/index.css` (custom CSS variables/classes — not Tailwind)
- Path alias `@/` → `src/`

## Code Style
- Functional components with hooks
- Component / page names: PascalCase (e.g. `DashboardPage.tsx`, `DataTable.tsx`)
- Keep components small and focused
- Prefer TypeScript types over loose `any`
- Reuse existing hooks (`useAsyncData`, `useClientPagination`, OCI job hooks) before inventing new ones

## Project Structure
- Pages → `src/pages/<domain>/`
- Shared UI → `src/components/`
- Hooks → `src/hooks/`
- Auth → `src/context/AuthContext.tsx`
- API client / types → `src/api/client.ts`
- OCI / dashboard domain logic → `src/oci/`, `src/dashboard/`
- Routes → `src/App.tsx`; shell / nav → `src/components/Layout.tsx`

## Development
- Local: `npm run dev` (Vite proxies `/api` per `vite.config.ts`)
- API base: `VITE_API_URL` (see `src/api/client.ts`)
- Edit `src/` directly; `old_files/` is archived BSS pipeline — not the edit path
